Clinical Recommendations: Hearing is within normal limits bilaterally, apart from a slight loss at 2kHz in the right ear. All other frequencies are within normal limits. Annual monitoring is recommended.

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: Please book a pap smear,mammogram&colonoscopy for cancer screening. Do a bone density when you go for your mammogram to check for any early signs of osteoporosis.
Comment Key: ClinicalExamComment
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Nurse: Lebo Cindi
Clinical Recommendations: Hearing is within normal limits bilaterally, apart from a slight loss at 2kHz in the right ear. All other frequencies are within normal limits. Annual monitoring is recommended.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: Maybe add 2x a week strengthening to your exercise routine so that you maintain muscle mass and bone strength.

Comment Value: Need repeat Mammogram, Dental check up done. Natural menopause, PAPsmear due
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Overview Notes: Try to avoid screens 2 hours before bed. Sleep in a dark room, preferably not the same place where you work/do other activities. Sleepio.com is a good resource
Comment Key: LabTestNote
Comment Value: Need to book for PAPsmear
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: You have no modifiable risk factors. You cholesterol is minimally high but so is your HDL (good cholesterol) so I am not concerned about this.
Comment Key: LifestyleNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Clinical Recommendations: Hearing is within normal limits bilaterally, apart from a slight loss at 2kHz in the right ear. All other frequencies are within normal limits. Annual monitoring is recommended.
Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: Maybe add 2x a week strengthening to your exercise routine so that you maintain muscle mass and bone strength.

Nurse: Lebo Cindi

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: You have no modifiable risk factors. You cholesterol is minimally high but so is your HDL (good cholesterol) so I am not concerned about this.

Overview Notes: Please book a pap smear,mammogram&colonoscopy for cancer screening. Do a bone density when you go for your mammogram to check for any early signs of osteoporosis.
Comment Key: MentalHealthStressRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Comment Key: ReportRecommendation
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist

Men's Health Recommendations:

Overview Notes: You have no modifiable risk factors. You cholesterol is minimally high but so is your HDL (good cholesterol) so I am not concerned about this.

Men's Health Recommendations: 
Women's Health Recommendations: Visit a general practitioner or a gynaecologists for a Pap smear and a Radiologist for a mammogram
Overview Notes: Urine sent to lab for microscopy and culture
Needs GP review to see if this resolves and to discuss results
Comment Key: WomensHealthNote
Comment Value: None
Special Investigation Notes: 4 plus blood in dipstix, urine sent for MCS and will need a review and ? refer to urologist
